Sentencas: The solid solubility limit of Ce in Nd2-x Ce (x) CuO4 +/- delta , prepared by sol-gel process, is established up to x = 0.2.
Titulo: Study of Nd2-x Ce x CuO4 ± δ (x=0.1-0.25) as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The transition from negative temperature coefficient to positive temperature coefficient, within the solid solubility region, is observed at 620 A degrees C.
Titulo: Study of Nd2-x Ce x CuO4 ± δ (x=0.1-0.25) as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The area-specific-resistance (ASR) is optimized for electrochemical cell sintered at 800 A degrees C. ASR enhances with increase in sintering temperature of cell.
Titulo: Study of Nd2-x Ce x CuO4 ± δ (x=0.1-0.25) as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: ASR value of 0.93 ohm cm(2) at 700 A degrees C, determined by electrochemical impedance spectroscopy is comparable against that by voltage versus current (V-I) characteristics at 0.98 ohm cm(2) at the same temperature.
Titulo: Study of Nd2-x Ce x CuO4 ± δ (x=0.1-0.25) as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Titulo: Study of Nd2-x Ce x CuO4 ± δ (x=0.1-0.25) as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
